Set of URLs for lookup services. Defaults align with GeoGratis APIs.
Endpoint URL for Geo Names service
Endpoint URL for Geo Location service
Endpoint URL for Geo Province service

Various settings for the geosearch fixture

Comma separated  that filters the search results based on the type of the geographical names. Allowed values can be found here (if using the Canadian GeoNames Search Service API): http://geogratis.gc.ca/services/geoname/en/codes /concise. Street address type ('ADDR') is also valid.

Comma separated list indicating the sort order of the defined 'categories'. Any missing categories are appended to the bottom of the sorted list. The results can still be sorted through this option even if there are no categories being filtered.

The maximum number of results to return per request. The Canadian GeoNames Search Service API has a 1000 search limit which will be used as an upper limit of results returned unless another service is being used with a higher limit.
Whether to return only official names for the geographic names. Default is false which will return both official names and formerly official names.
